    "Considering the problem of data leakage approached from the lens of access, this application is natural.",
    "A user querying for their own personally identifiable information should, ideally, be able to access it whereas an unauthorized user should not.",
    "Obfuscating portions or the entirety of a corpus using zero-knowledge proofs [133] allows for untrusted training nodes, or the model itself, to act on sensitive data without the ability to regurgitate it to a potentially malicious party.",
    "This same mechanism has broad applications that have been explored in other recent works as well, with special focuses on ZKPs for data curation and pre-processing [113], which consequently enhance passive privacy within LLMs.",
